WEBVTT

00:03:59.145 --> 00:04:00.935
I joined the Harvard Medical School

00:04:00.959 --> 00:04:03.801
and Brigham and Women's Hospital
Division of Global Health.

00:04:03.825 --> 00:04:05.059
And I, as a researcher,

00:04:05.083 --> 00:04:07.737
really wanted to get started
on this problem right away.

00:04:07.761 --> 00:04:11.329
I was like, "How do we reduce
the crushing vulnerability

00:04:11.353 --> 00:04:15.124
of people living in these types
of fragile settings?

00:04:15.148 --> 00:04:17.617
Is there any way
we can start to think about

00:04:17.641 --> 00:04:20.346
how to protect and quickly recover

00:04:20.370 --> 00:04:23.179
the institutions
that are critical to survival,

00:04:23.203 --> 00:04:24.716
like the health system?"

00:04:24.740 --> 00:04:28.061
And I have to say,
I had amazing colleagues.

